# Shell by platform

Pick the shell from **user_info** (`OS Version`, `Shell`). Do not use zsh.

**On native Windows (`OS Version: win32`, `Shell: powershell`), this rule overrides any user preference to "use bash for testing".** Cursor's Shell tool runs **Windows PowerShell 5.1** (`ps-script-*.ps1`), not bash and not PowerShell 7+.

## Linux or WSL (bash)

When `Shell` is **bash** (native Linux, macOS, or WSL):

- Run tests and terminal commands in **bash**
- Use bash syntax: `&&`, `|`, heredocs, `/home/...` or `/mnt/c/...` paths in WSL
- Prefer bash for scripts and interactive commands in this environment

```bash
cd "/mnt/c/Users/tobid/Dropbox/GitHub/SensorsINI/jaer" && ant compile
```

## Native Windows (PowerShell 5.1)

When `OS Version` is **win32** and `Shell` is **powershell**:

- Run commands in **PowerShell** directly — do **not** wrap in `bash -lc` / `bash -c`
- Use `;` to chain commands ( **`&&` is invalid in PS 5.1** )
- Use Windows paths (`C:\Users\...` or `C:/Users/...`)
- Use PowerShell cmdlets instead of Unix tools:

| Bash | PowerShell 5.1 |
|------|----------------|
| `cmd1 && cmd2` | `cmd1; if ($?) { cmd2 }` or just `cmd1; cmd2` |
| `\| tail -20` | `\| Select-Object -Last 20` |
| `\| head -20` | `\| Select-Object -First 20` |
| `2>&1 \| tee f` | `*>&1 \| Tee-Object f` |
| `export VAR=val` | `$env:VAR = "val"` |
| `$(cat <<'EOF' ... EOF)` | `git commit -m "Title" -m "Body"` |

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\tobid\Dropbox\GitHub\SensorsINI\jaer"; ant compile 2>&1 | Select-Object -Last 20
```

Before every Shell tool call on Windows, mentally check: **no `&&`, no `tail`/`head`, no heredocs**.

## Do not

- Use PowerShell on Linux/WSL when bash is the configured shell
- Use bash syntax or Git Bash wrappers on native Windows when PowerShell is the configured shell
- Use zsh

## Scripts in the repo

- `.sh` files: bash (Linux/WSL/CI); edit with bash syntax regardless of host OS
- `.ps1` files: PowerShell on Windows
